Interface VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods.VBiFunction<A1,A2,R>

  • Type Parameters:
    A1 - the generic type of the first argument
    A2 - the generic type of the second argument
    R - the generic type of the return value, with VoidR as a possibility
    All Superinterfaces:
    BiFunction<A1,A2,R>
    Enclosing interface:
    VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods.VBiFunction<A1,A2,R>
extends BiFunction<A1,A2,R>
    A "voidable" functional interface which takes two args of any generic types <A1,A2> and returns a value of any generic type <R> including VoidR.

    Function objects of the following types may be converted to this type:

    1. BiConsumer<A1,A2> -> VBiFunction<A1,A2,VoidR>
    2. BiFunction<A1,A2,R> -> VBiFunction<A1,A2,R>
    VBiFunctions made from BiConsumer<A1,A2> return voidR; VBiFunctions made from BiFunction<A1,A2,R> return objects of generic type <R>.
